(41, 'Top 5 Healthiest Foods in the World!', 'FOOD & NIGHTLIFE', 'JULY 25,2017', '<p style="text-align="center""><i>Now get fit, without even having to give up eating!!!</i>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<p>\r\nWell one thing is eating &amp one is eating smart. Which one do you choose? Here are the food items that you should definitely include in your everyday meals!\r\n</p>\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Lemons</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n<br>\r\nHow to consume them?\r\n<br>\r\nLemons can add an amazing flavor to a couple of things, rice for instance can be cooked very well with lemon. Alternatively, you can add it to your green tea or have it \r\nwith a mix of hot water and honey.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWhy Lemon?<br>\r\nOne lemon a day fulfills a person&#39;s 100 percent vitamin C needs. It has been speculated that they can prevent cancer by slowing the growth of certain cells. They&#39;re also widely \r\nknown for their anti-oxidant properties.\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/hd5.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <span class="caption text-muted">Lemons</span>\r\n<br>\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Broccoli</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n<br>\r\nHow to consume it?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt definitely isn''t a favorite food item, especially among children. Some interesting ways to include it in your meals are to cook it with rice, mixed vegetables or even as a pizza topping!\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWhy Broccoli?\r\n<br>\r\nIt is rich in Vitamin K, B1, B2, B6, B9, Amino Acid, Sodium, Potassium and is known to have more Vitamin E than olive oil. Basically itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s really healthy!\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/hd1.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <span class="caption text-muted">Broccoli</span>\r\n<br>\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Dark Chocolate</h2>\r\n<p><br>\r\nHow to consume it?\r\n<br>\r\nWell, unwrap the bar and eat it! But be careful not to eat too much at a time. Have a cube with a glass of milk. Use it to sweeten or flavor the milk.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWhy Dark Chocolate?\r\n<br>\r\nIt is a lesser known fact that dark chocolate is good for your heart. It is rich in antioxidants and flavonoids. It also helps in keeping a check on the blood pressure & stubborn cholesterol.\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><br>\r\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/hd4.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <span class="caption text-muted">Dark Chocolate</span>\r\n<br>\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Potato (Surprise! Surprise!)\r\n\r\n</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n<br>\r\nHow to consume them?\r\n<br>\r\nWell, obviously not as chips from the packet. In fact potatoes in any packaged form will not bring you any benefits. Boiled potatoes in salads, or as hash browns or even as fries are the way to go!\r\nBaked potatoes taste good too!\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWhy Potatoes? \r\n<br>\r\nPotatoes contain cell building folates, fight cancerous cells and help in making the immune system strong! \r\nThey also contain good carbs!\r\n<br>\r\n</p>\r\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/hd2.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <span class="caption text-muted">Potatoes</span>\r\n<h2 class="section-heading">Walnuts</h2>\r\n<p>\r\nHow to consume them?<br>\r\nEat it as it is. Garnish your oats with walnuts, bake them with cakes and bread or soak them in milk!\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\nWhy walnuts?<br>\r\n\r\nThey contain Omega-3 Fatty Acids which are known to assist in maintaining cholesterol levels.\r\nThey may even prevent us from damage against the sun!\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/hd6.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    \r\n                    <span class="caption text-muted">Walnuts</span>\r\n<br>\r\n', 'Artika Singh', 'healthy.png', 'hd6.jpg'),
(45, 'Nuts about Coconut Oil Yet?', 'BEAUTY & WELLNESS', 'August 24,2017', '\n<p><b>If flared pants and polka dots can make a comeback, then why leave vintage health and beauty trends!</b></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Our moms and grand moms have probably been trying hard to make us see the multiple benefits of <b>coconut oil</b> for years. But obviously we are quicker at noticing something we read in a magazine or hear online than paying attention to them! I, following their footsteps, will once again try to prove that coconut oil is indeed the <b>BEST</b>. And this is truly, completely & wholly based on my personal experience.</p>\n<br><br>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/coconut1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Coconut</span>\n\n  \n<h2 class="section-heading">\n1.	Magic Potion for skin and hair!!!</h2>\n<br>\n\n<p>\n\nTraditionally coconut oil is known to be an <b>excellent moisturizer </b>coupled with that it’s anti-oxidant properties makes it the perfect remedy for not only dry and flaky skin but also degenerative skin problems like dermatitis, eczema, premature ageing, psoriasis and other such infections. So get some coconut oil massage everyday & save yourself from paying those hefty bills at a dermatologist’s clinic.\n\nAnd ladies and gentlemen trying <b>to fight hair loss and hair damage</b>, have you tried this yet? Coconut oil prevents your hair from losing healthy proteins thereby giving you healthy, shiny and strong and lice free hair.</p>\n<br>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/coconut2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Healthy Hair with coconut oil!</span>\n\n\n \n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n2.	Want whiter underarms?</h2>\n<br>\n\n<p>\nCoconut Oil is the answer! I actually learnt about this from my dermatologist when I went in for <b>underarms lightening</b> procedure. She asked me to avoid the procedure and try this home remedy instead. And… it worked!! Our underarm skin & inner side of upper thighs tend to get discolored as it is subjected continuously to friction. Fix this by applying coconut oil on the affected areas, two times in a day! Yes, it’s really that simple!\n</p>\n\n<br><br>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/coconut3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Lightened Underarms</span>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n3.	Way to a healthier heart</h2>\n\n<br>\n\n<p>Contrary to popular belief, coconut oil, unlike other saturated fat sources, is <b>beneficial for the human heart.</b> It is known to contain 50 percent Lauric acid, which helps in preventing both high cholesterol and blood pressure. Consuming coconut oil keeps the arteries healthy and lowers the chances of heart diseases.\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/coconut4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Healthy Heart</span>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n4.	Weight Loss</h2>\n\n<br>\n\n\n<p>Yes you heard it right! Ok let’s bring down that excitement by just a notch. You still need to exercise but including coconut oil in your diet will definitely <b>increase the rate of weight loss.</b> Scientifically, coconut oil contains short and medium length fatty acid chains which can be broken down more easily. In lay man’s term, it’s easier to digest! With regulation of metabolism it further adds to the weight loss. </p>\n\n\n<br><br>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/coconut5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Weight Loss</span>\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n5.	A Shining Smile Please!</h2>\n\n<br>\n\n\n<p>Coconut oil facilitates the absorption of calcium, major component of our teeth, in our body! Coconut oil thus helps in maintaining stronger, <b>healthier and whiter teeth,</b> avoiding root infections and most of all, saving us from the horror of visiting the dentist!\n</p>\n<br><br>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1" src="img/coconut6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Shiny Smile</span>\n\n\n\n\n', 'Artika Singh', 'coconut.png', 'coconut1.jpg');

